1
00:00:01,700 --> 00:00:08,150
Before we move forward, let me walk you through on what are my expectations before you take the course.

2
00:00:08,630 --> 00:00:11,780
This course has a very few prerequisites.

3
00:00:11,930 --> 00:00:12,920
As you know.

4
00:00:12,920 --> 00:00:16,890
We will be learning ASP.NET Core MVC in this course.

5
00:00:16,910 --> 00:00:22,970
Because of that, you must have a basic understanding of the C-sharp programming language.

6
00:00:23,240 --> 00:00:28,300
If you have worked with the traditional .net applications, that is completely okay.

7
00:00:28,310 --> 00:00:34,820
As long as you understand the basic foundations of C#, you should be good with the course.

8
00:00:35,650 --> 00:00:40,300
On top of that, we will be using SQL Server for our database.

9
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:45,280
So you should have some experience in writing queries for SQL Server.

10
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:53,560
I do not want any fancy experience like functions and anything complex, but basic SQL like select statement,

11
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:57,310
delete statements and those basic SQL syntax.

12
00:00:57,340 --> 00:00:59,410
You should be familiar with them.

13
00:00:59,710 --> 00:01:05,860
As long as you have these two basic foundations, you will not face any issue in the course.

14
00:01:06,190 --> 00:01:13,870
I will be starting from Ground zero when it comes to explaining .net core MVC and how everything comes

15
00:01:13,870 --> 00:01:14,770
together.

16
00:01:15,690 --> 00:01:19,080
With that, let me continue from the next video.

